  steps:
  - instructionText: 'The objective is to move all the cards to the foundations

      -
      Stack them by <color=#ffa84a>category</color>

      - Start with a category
      card

      - To move a card, drag it.'
    movements:
    - cardName: Happy
      isCategory: 1
      toContainerType: 2
      toContainerIndex: 0
    - cardName: Joyful
      isCategory: 0
      toContainerType: 2
      toContainerIndex: 0
    - cardName: Medieval
      isCategory: 1
      toContainerType: 2
      toContainerIndex: 1
  - instructionText: 'Doing good!

      - You can also move cards <color=#ffa84a>between
      columns</color>

      - You can stack them if they are in the <color=#ffa84a>same
      category</color>'
    movements:
    - cardName: Pastry
      isCategory: 0
      toContainerType: 3
      toContainerIndex: 1
  - instructionText: "Needing more cards? \n- Check the <color=#ffa84a>draw pile</color>
      by tapping on the top right"
    movements:
    - cardName: Delighted
      isCategory: 0
      toContainerType: 1
      toContainerIndex: 0
    - cardName: Delighted
      isCategory: 0
      toContainerType: 2
      toContainerIndex: 0
    - cardName: Cheerful
      isCategory: 0
      toContainerType: 2
      toContainerIndex: 0
  - instructionText: Once a category gets completed in the foundation, it gets <color=#ffa84a>cleared</color>
      and you can <color=#ffa84a>start a new category</color> there.
    movements:
    - cardName: Desserts
      isCategory: 1
      toContainerType: 2
      toContainerIndex: 0
  - instructionText: Excellent! You now have an <color=#ffa84a>empty column.</color>
      You can move a full stack of cards there.
    movements:
    - cardName: Sweet
      isCategory: 0
      toContainerType: 3
      toContainerIndex: 0
